The All Progressives Congress (APC) in Rivers state has raised the alarm over an impostor hiding under the guise of having the authority of the National Working Committee (NWC) of the APC to appeal the judgement of the Rivers State High Court which confirmed Hon. Igo Aguma as caretaker committee chairman of the party. A statement signed by Media Adviser to the APC Caretaker Committee chairman, Livingstone Wechie, and made available to LEADERSHIP Friday in Abuja, said that the National Working Committee of the APC did not authorise anybody or group to represent the party or file an appeal against the judgement on behalf of the party. It said that filing an appeal on behalf of the party by anyone would amount to criminal impersonation of the APC National Working Committee. The statement said the “National Working Committee of the APC has not taken any decision whether or not to appeal the judgement of the Court on this issue. “The general public, APC members and all relevant institutions are advised to take notice of this press statement and disregard as well as discountenance these desperate moves by the said individuals seeking to mislead the public and APC members,” the statement added.